immunity (0.5) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Mount /proc directly and read only instead of bind mounting it.

 -- Torsten Werner <twerner@debian.org>  Sat, 11 Apr 2009 22:01:37 +0200

immunity (0.4) experimental; urgency=low

  * Explicitly create .Xauthority file in trusted mode.
  * Change default command from "/bin/sh" to "/bin/bash".
  * Copy device nodes instead of bind mounting them.
  * Bump up Standards-Version: 3.8.1 (no changes).
  * Remove supplementary group "audio" again.
  * Add /etc/mailcap to bind mounts.

 -- Torsten Werner <twerner@debian.org>  Fri, 10 Apr 2009 23:04:37 +0200

immunity (0.3) experimental; urgency=low

  * Lock down the browser process.
  * Disable suid and sgid binaries for tmpfs.
  * Disable device files and suid and sgid binaries by remounting "/".
  * Do no longer make /tmp world writable.
  * Remove unused functions from the Python module.
  * Put shadow user into supplementary group "audio".
  * Remove last reference to tmp directory.
  * Improve INSTALL file.

 -- Torsten Werner <twerner@debian.org>  Fri, 20 Mar 2009 22:30:50 +0100

immunity (0.2) experimental; urgency=low

  * Use a private namespace.
  * Fake up a fully different filesystem.
  * Allow executing user specified command.
  * Change default command to /bin/sh.
  * Add capability support.
  * Drop most capabilities early.
  * Do no longer create a separate tmp directory.

 -- Torsten Werner <twerner@debian.org>  Sun, 15 Mar 2009 16:29:24 +0100

